------------------------------------------------------------
16.using pipe operator (|), cut, sort, uniq, head commands, sort ip addresses by their
counts in 'apache_logs' file and append top 10 results into 'answer' file.


[labuser@redhat lab]$ cut -d '-' -f 1 /tmp/logs/apache.log | sort | uniq -c | sort -nr | head -10
    482 66.249.73.135
    364 46.105.14.53
    357 130.237.218.86
    273 75.97.9.59
    113 50.16.19.13
    102 209.85.238.199
     99 68.180.224.225
     84 100.43.83.137
     83 208.115.111.72
     82 198.46.149.143

-------------------------------------------------------------
17.use 'sha256sum' command to get shasum of your 'answer' file.

[labuser@redhat lab]$ sha256sum answer.txt
b968323b3cf09344b6788457cad614430d6e22be2a19e7d816a74036369ad152  answer.txt


